rrison is an extremely common surname in northern England. One important and influential American family of bearers are descended from Benjamin Harrison, who emigrated from England to VA in 1633 or 1634. Descendants include another Benjamin Harrison (<i>c.</i> 1726–91), who was an activist in the American Revolution and a signer of the Declaration of Independence. His son William Henry Harrison (1773–1841) and great-grandson Benjamin Harrison (1833–1901) both became presidents of the US."],"variants":[{"name":"Harry","meanings":["English (mainly south Wales and southwestern England): from the medieval personal name <i>Harry</i>, a common form of   Henry  , with assimilation of <i>-nr-</i> to <i>-rr-</i> and regular Middle English change of <i>-er-</i> to <i>-ar-</i>. In south Wales the surname is generally a post-medieval coinage, in most cases not hereditary until the 18th or 19th century.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Hariric</i>, composed of the elements <i>hari</i>, <i>heri</i> ‘army’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power(ful)’.","Native American (e.g. Navajo): adoption of the English personal name <i>Harry</i> (see 1 above) as a surname."]},{"name":"Arrizon","meanings":["Hispanic (mainly Mexico): probably an altered form of English   Harrison  ."]},{"name":"Harison","meanings":["English: variant of   Harrison  ."]},{"name":"Arrison","meanings":["English: variant of   Harrison  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Harrison was born in 1514, in Sproughton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. He died in September 1576, in Nayland, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 62."},"et":{"1514–September 1576":"1514–september 1576","1504–1574":"1504–1574","1539–1601":"1539–1601","1514–1576":"1514–1576","1514":"1514","1601":"1601","1576":"1576","1574":"1574","September 1576":"september 1576","1539":"1539","1504":"1504","Sproughton, Suffolk, England":"Sproughton, Suffolk, England","Bildeston, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Bildeston, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nayland, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Nayland, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sproughton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Sproughton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1514–September 1576":"1514–syyskuu 1576","1504–1574":"1504–1574","1539–1601":"1539–1601","1514–1576":"1514–1576","1514":"1514","1601":"1601","1576":"1576","1574":"1574","September 1576":"syyskuu 1576","1539":"1539","1504":"1504","Sproughton, Suffolk, England":"Sproughton, Suffolk, England","Bildeston, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Bildeston, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Nayland, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Nayland, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sproughton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Sproughton, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1514–September 1576":"1514–septembre 1576","1504–1574":"1504–1574","1539–1601":"1539–1601","1514–1576":"1514–1576","1514":"1514","1601":"1601","1576":"1576","1574":"1574","September 1576":"septembre 1576","1539":"1539","1504":"1504","Sproughton, Suffolk, England":"Sproughton, Suffolk, Angleterre","Bildeston, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Bildeston, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Nayland, Suffolk, England, Unite